column5: Just found out grandpa has some property up there on the Trent-Severn (sp?) waterway....can't seem to find any info....would be curious to see if anyone knows the area

I pass thru Washago on the way up to the Parry Sound area.  It's right at the north end of Lake Couchiching....some good fishing there!  I also have a few friends that moved there from the Toronto area and they love it.  Casino Rama is close by as well.  Here's a few links for you.... http://www.washago.ca/main.html  http://www.washagocruiselines.com/
